248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.10fa2afa-153e-4c47-9c68-717596a6c4d7.prompt=String to Append \: 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.11eb309b-bdbe-4b5e-8edc-c90376f2b215.description=Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.1ecdfe9a-0bc4-46a5-84d5-02c099080290.prompt=String to Append \: 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.29237c5b-3fce-4fe0-9ed0-7e426474ab1d.prompt=Enter a value for List 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.75e2aacb-5c67-4ca4-91ca-f90911c4d8ba.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.

248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.a96b407f-ba59-4f72-a60e-987677287733.prompt=Delimiter\: 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.adea06a0-8e47-4461-b184-7d54b05b2cb0.prompt=Delimiter\: 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.b319a1a6-ef9b-4d31-b9c3-69656a696613.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Returns\: The value in the specified key. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.dd6e5d49-9fa7-49d2-9ee3-b17ba57438bc.prompt=Enter a value for toMatch 248c19a5-778e-454b-8b0d-321fa128cc72.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match to the value specified in the input "compareTo" based on the input "matchType".  

Inputs\:
list - The list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Results\:
others -  A delimiter delimited list of elements that do not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.
